Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportPowerRoute(25.10)                                reportPowerRoute(25.10)

Name
       reportPowerRoute - Reports the cut ratio when two types of cuts are in-
       serted  between two parallel followpin rails with editPowerVia -follow-
       pin_via_stapling to maximize the effective number of cuts

Syntax
       reportPowerRoute

       [-help]

        [-followpin_cut_ratio {<cutClass1 weight1 cutClass2 weight2>}]

        [-net <string>]

       Reports the cut ratio when two types of cuts are inserted  between  two
       parallel  followpin  rails with editPowerVia -followpin_via_stapling to
       maximize the effective number of cuts. The ratio is calculated  by  di-
       viding  the  sum of weighted cut count of each cut class by theoretical
       cut count, if the smallest via is inserted along with  the  power  rail
       with minimum spacing.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each reportPowerRoute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man reportPowerRoute

       -followpin_cut_ratio {<cutClass1 weight1 cutClass2 weight2>}
              Specifies  the  names  and  weights  of the two types of the cut
              classes.

              Note: The cutClass must be defined in the header lef file before
              loading  the  design.  Otherwise,  it  will  print  error   mes-
              sage(IMPPP-4411). Additionally, the format of the cutClass to be
              defined in the lef file should be:

              PROPERTYDEFINITIONS

              ^aEUR| ^aEUR|

              LAYER LEF58_CUTCLASS STRING ;

              ^aEUR| ^aEUR|

              END PROPERTYDEFINITIONS

              LAYER VIA0

              TYPE CUT ;

              PROPERTY LEF58_CUTCLASS "

              CUTCLASS VSINGLECUT WIDTH 0.020 LENGTH 0.020 CUTS 1;

              CUTCLASS VDOUBLECUT WIDTH 0.020 LENGTH 0.050 CUTS 2;

              " ;

              ^aEUR| ^aEUR|

              END VIA0

       -net <string>
              Specifies  the followpin net names to be reported. If this para-
              meter is not specified, the report is  calculated  for  all  the
              followpin nets.

Example
       The following command specifies the weights for the VDOUBLE and VSINGLE
       cut classes and calculates the reports for the VSS followpin net:

       reportPowerRoute -followpin_cut_ratio {VDOUBLE 1.8 VSINGLE 1} -net VSS

Related Information
       Power Planning and Routing chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

